BGL Core Processor tool

Coreprocessor is a basic parallel debugger that can be used to examine BlueGene/L compute node corefiles or attach to running partions via mmcs.  When attached to mmcs, coreprocessor uses the low-level JTAG interface (via the BG/L service network) to extract the debug information.  

Advantages:
 - OS can be completely dead and handles debug
 - Quick isolation of nodes that abnormal
 - Scales to 131,072 processors

Limitations:
 - no breakpoints
 - no visibility

To see the usage information:
  ./coreprocessor.pl -h				(show help text)

